<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-30-1068 </DOCNO><TEXT>In the wet flue gas washer for removing sulfur dioxide from the stackgases of fossil-fired power stations with a washing liquid, which containscalcium, lime or other suppliers of calcium ions and which has a onebase and/or multibase carbonic acid, preferably formic acid, added asthe additive, the washing liquid is additionally exposed to ethylenediamine tetra-acetic acid, which produces extensive separation of NO/subx/ in the same process.</TEXT></DOC>